This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it addresses the problem of RGBD object recognition. It also involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks (DCNN) and object detection, which are common topics in the computer vision field. 

The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) as it proposes a real-time detection and recognition pipeline, which can be applied to robotic systems. 

Machine learning (cs.LG) is another likely sub-category as the paper proposes a novel weakly-supervised learning architecture that combines parametric and non-parametric models. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to solve a real-world problem. 

Finally, multimedia (cs.MM) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of multi-modal DCNN for object recognition, which can be applied to multimedia data.
